{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":106,"text":"So the machine I'm going to talk you about"},{"time":1530,"text":"is what I call the greatest machine that never was."},{"time":3204,"text":"It was a machine that was never built,"},{"time":5203,"text":"and yet, it will be built."},{"time":7583,"text":"It was a machine that was designed"},{"time":9575,"text":"long before anyone thought about computers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11926,"text":"If you know anything about the history of computers,"},{"time":14075,"text":"you will know that in the '30s and the '40s,"},{"time":16595,"text":"simple computers were created"},{"time":19150,"text":"that started the computer revolution we have today,"},{"time":21943,"text":"and you would be correct,"},{"time":23229,"text":"except for you'd have the wrong century."},{"time":25711,"text":"The first computer was really designed"},{"time":27351,"text":"in the 1830s and 1840s, not the 1930s and 1940s."},{"time":31023,"text":"It was designed, and parts of it were prototyped,"},{"time":33351,"text":"and the bits of it that were built are here"},{"time":35487,"text":"in South Kensington."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37480,"text":"That machine was built by this guy, Charles Babbage."},{"time":40799,"text":"Now, I have a great affinity for Charles Babbage"},{"time":42555,"text":"because his hair is always completely unkempt like this"},{"time":45164,"text":"in every single picture. (Laughter)"},{"time":47505,"text":"He was a very wealthy man, and a sort of,"},{"time":49352,"text":"part of the aristocracy of Britain,"},{"time":51365,"text":"and on a Saturday night in Marylebone,"},{"time":53704,"text":"were you part of the intelligentsia of that period,"},{"time":56135,"text":"you would have been invited round to his house"},{"time":57631,"text":"for a soiree — and he invited everybody:"},{"time":60590,"text":"kings, the Duke of Wellington, many, many famous people —"},{"time":64022,"text":"and he would have shown you one of his mechanical machines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66543,"text":"I really miss that era, you know, where you could"},{"time":69583,"text":"go around for a soiree and see a mechanical computer"},{"time":71931,"text":"get demonstrated to you. (Laughter)"},{"time":73044,"text":"But Babbage, Babbage himself was born"},{"time":76310,"text":"at the end of the 18th century,"},{"time":78044,"text":"and was a fairly famous mathematician."},{"time":80088,"text":"He held the post that Newton held at Cambridge,"},{"time":83231,"text":"and that was recently held by Stephen Hawking."},{"time":85743,"text":"He's less well known than either of them because"},{"time":88598,"text":"he got this idea to make mechanical computing devices"},{"time":91748,"text":"and never made any of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94033,"text":"The reason he never made any of them, he's a classic nerd."},{"time":97318,"text":"Every time he had a good idea, he'd think,"},{"time":99329,"text":"\"That's brilliant, I'm going to start building that one."},{"time":100777,"text":"I'll spend a fortune on it. I've got a better idea."},{"time":103372,"text":"I'm going to work on this one. (Laughter) And I'm going to do this one.\""},{"time":105732,"text":"He did this until Sir Robert Peel, then Prime Minister,"},{"time":108612,"text":"basically kicked him out of Number 10 Downing Street,"},{"time":111076,"text":"and kicking him out, in those days, that meant saying,"},{"time":113517,"text":"\"I bid you good day, sir.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116669,"text":"The thing he designed was this monstrosity here,"},{"time":118649,"text":"the analytical engine. Now, just to give you an idea of this,"},{"time":122088,"text":"this is a view from above."},{"time":123960,"text":"Every one of these circles is a cog, a stack of cogs,"},{"time":127073,"text":"and this thing is as big as a steam locomotive."},{"time":130309,"text":"So as I go through this talk, I want you to imagine"},{"time":132300,"text":"this gigantic machine. We heard those wonderful sounds"},{"time":134944,"text":"of what this thing would have sounded like."},{"time":136704,"text":"And I'm going to take you through the architecture of the machine"},{"time":138481,"text":"— that's why it's computer architecture —"},{"time":139960,"text":"and tell you about this machine, which is a computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143287,"text":"So let's talk about the memory. The memory"},{"time":146690,"text":"is very like the memory of a computer today,"},{"time":148937,"text":"except it was all made out of metal,"},{"time":151639,"text":"stacks and stacks of cogs, 30 cogs high."},{"time":155183,"text":"Imagine a thing this high of cogs,"},{"time":157253,"text":"hundreds and hundreds of them,"},{"time":159008,"text":"and they've got numbers on them."},{"time":160898,"text":"It's a decimal machine. Everything's done in decimal."},{"time":163317,"text":"And he thought about using binary. The problem"},{"time":164902,"text":"with using binary is that the machine would have been so"},{"time":166620,"text":"tall, it would have been ridiculous. As it is, it's enormous."},{"time":169937,"text":"So he's got memory."},{"time":171996,"text":"The memory is this bit over here."},{"time":174403,"text":"You see it all like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176733,"text":"This monstrosity over here is the CPU, the chip, if you like."},{"time":181268,"text":"Of course, it's this big."},{"time":183518,"text":"Completely mechanical. This whole machine is mechanical."},{"time":186431,"text":"This is a picture of a prototype for part of the CPU"},{"time":190572,"text":"which is in the Science Museum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192711,"text":"The CPU could do the four fundamental functions of arithmetic --"},{"time":196343,"text":"so addition, multiplication, subtraction, division --"},{"time":198796,"text":"which already is a bit of a feat in metal,"},{"time":201804,"text":"but it could also do something that a computer does"},{"time":204433,"text":"and a calculator doesn't:"},{"time":206132,"text":"this machine could look at its own internal memory and make a decision."},{"time":210070,"text":"It could do the \"if then\" for basic programmers,"},{"time":212936,"text":"and that fundamentally made it into a computer."},{"time":215076,"text":"It could compute. It couldn't just calculate. It could do more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219674,"text":"Now, if we look at this, and we stop for a minute,"},{"time":222355,"text":"and we think about chips today, we can't"},{"time":224226,"text":"look inside a silicon chip. It's just so tiny."},{"time":228041,"text":"Yet if you did, you would see something"},{"time":229842,"text":"very, very similar to this."},{"time":231664,"text":"There's this incredible complexity in the CPU,"},{"time":234611,"text":"and this incredible regularity in the memory."},{"time":237303,"text":"If you've ever seen an electron microscope picture,"},{"time":238965,"text":"you'll see this. This all looks the same,"},{"time":240934,"text":"then there's this bit over here which is incredibly complicated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243500,"text":"All this cog wheel mechanism here is doing is what a computer does,"},{"time":247483,"text":"but of course you need to program this thing, and of course,"},{"time":249576,"text":"Babbage used the technology of the day"},{"time":252601,"text":"and the technology that would reappear in the '50s, '60s and '70s,"},{"time":256247,"text":"which is punch cards. This thing over here"},{"time":259116,"text":"is one of three punch card readers in here,"},{"time":261940,"text":"and this is a program in the Science Museum, just"},{"time":265620,"text":"not far from here, created by Charles Babbage,"},{"time":270013,"text":"that is sitting there — you can go see it —"},{"time":271881,"text":"waiting for the machine to be built."},{"time":274322,"text":"And there's not just one of these, there's many of them."},{"time":277742,"text":"He prepared programs anticipating this would happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280832,"text":"Now, the reason they used punch cards was that Jacquard,"},{"time":282805,"text":"in France, had created the Jacquard loom,"},{"time":284977,"text":"which was weaving these incredible patterns controlled by punch cards,"},{"time":287655,"text":"so he was just repurposing the technology of the day,"},{"time":290287,"text":"and like everything else he did, he's using the technology"},{"time":292392,"text":"of his era, so 1830s, 1840s, 1850s, cogs, steam,"},{"time":297139,"text":"mechanical devices. Ironically, born the same year"},{"time":301077,"text":"as Charles Babbage was Michael Faraday,"},{"time":303249,"text":"who would completely revolutionize everything"},{"time":305926,"text":"with the dynamo, transformers, all these sorts of things."},{"time":308439,"text":"Babbage, of course, wanted to use proven technology,"},{"time":311597,"text":"so steam and things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313150,"text":"Now, he needed accessories."},{"time":314823,"text":"Obviously, you've got a computer now."},{"time":316495,"text":"You've got punch cards, a CPU and memory."},{"time":318884,"text":"You need accessories you're going to come with."},{"time":320819,"text":"You're not just going to have that,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":322447,"text":"So, first of all, you had sound. You had a bell,"},{"time":325275,"text":"so if anything went wrong — (Laughter) —"},{"time":327429,"text":"or the machine needed the attendant to come to it,"},{"time":329774,"text":"there was a bell it could ring. (Laughter)"},{"time":331744,"text":"And there's actually an instruction on the punch card"},{"time":333280,"text":"which says \"Ring the bell.\" So you can imagine this \"Ting!\""},{"time":336182,"text":"You know, just stop for a moment, imagine all those noises,"},{"time":338382,"text":"this thing, \"Click, clack click click click,\""},{"time":339463,"text":"steam engine, \"Ding,\" right? (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":342400,"text":"You also need a printer, obviously, and everyone needs a printer."},{"time":344835,"text":"This is actually a picture of the printing mechanism for"},{"time":347843,"text":"another machine of his, called the Difference Engine No. 2,"},{"time":350326,"text":"which he never built, but which the Science Museum"},{"time":352261,"text":"did build in the '80s and '90s."},{"time":354432,"text":"It's completely mechanical, again, a printer."},{"time":356707,"text":"It prints just numbers, because he was obsessed with numbers,"},{"time":359405,"text":"but it does print onto paper, and it even does word wrapping,"},{"time":362922,"text":"so if you get to the end of the line, it goes around like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365694,"text":"You also need graphics, right?"},{"time":367344,"text":"I mean, if you're going to do anything with graphics,"},{"time":368900,"text":"so he said, \"Well, I need a plotter. I've got a big piece of paper"},{"time":371496,"text":"and an ink pen and I'll make it plot.\""},{"time":373604,"text":"So he designed a plotter as well,"},{"time":375434,"text":"and, you know, at that point, I think he got pretty much"},{"time":379359,"text":"a pretty good machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380890,"text":"Along comes this woman, Ada Lovelace."},{"time":383580,"text":"Now, imagine these soirees, all these great and good comes along."},{"time":386301,"text":"This lady is the daughter of the mad, bad"},{"time":389393,"text":"and dangerous-to-know Lord Byron,"},{"time":391815,"text":"and her mother, being a bit worried that she might have"},{"time":394335,"text":"inherited some of Lord Byron's madness and badness,"},{"time":397192,"text":"thought, \"I know the solution: Mathematics is the solution."},{"time":400430,"text":"We'll teach her mathematics. That'll calm her down.\""},{"time":403379,"text":"(Laughter) Because of course,"},{"time":407135,"text":"there's never been a mathematician that's gone crazy,"},{"time":411050,"text":"so, you know, that'll be fine. (Laughter)"},{"time":413451,"text":"Everything'll be fine. So she's got this mathematical training,"},{"time":416789,"text":"and she goes to one of these soirees with her mother,"},{"time":419527,"text":"and Charles Babbage, you know, gets out his machine."},{"time":422317,"text":"The Duke of Wellington is there, you know,"},{"time":424151,"text":"get out the machine, obviously demonstrates it,"},{"time":425723,"text":"and she gets it. She's the only person in his lifetime, really,"},{"time":429474,"text":"who said, \"I understand what this does,"},{"time":430766,"text":"and I understand the future of this machine.\""},{"time":432973,"text":"And we owe to her an enormous amount because we know"},{"time":436060,"text":"a lot about the machine that Babbage was intending to build"},{"time":439037,"text":"because of her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440640,"text":"Now, some people call her the first programmer."},{"time":443397,"text":"This is actually from one of -- the paper that she translated."},{"time":446783,"text":"This is a program written in a particular style."},{"time":449694,"text":"It's not, historically, totally accurate that she's the first programmer,"},{"time":453263,"text":"and actually, she did something more amazing."},{"time":455316,"text":"Rather than just being a programmer,"},{"time":456886,"text":"she saw something that Babbage didn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459058,"text":"Babbage was totally obsessed with mathematics."},{"time":462242,"text":"He was building a machine to do mathematics,"},{"time":466191,"text":"and Lovelace said, \"You could do more than mathematics"},{"time":469450,"text":"on this machine.\" And just as you do,"},{"time":472285,"text":"everyone in this room already's got a computer on them"},{"time":473910,"text":"right now, because they've got a phone."},{"time":475964,"text":"If you go into that phone, every single thing in that phone"},{"time":478192,"text":"or computer or any other computing device"},{"time":480207,"text":"is mathematics. It's all numbers at the bottom."},{"time":482288,"text":"Whether it's video or text or music or voice, it's all numbers,"},{"time":486981,"text":"it's all, underlying it, mathematical functions happening,"},{"time":490961,"text":"and Lovelace said, \"Just because you're doing"},{"time":493066,"text":"mathematical functions and symbols"},{"time":496388,"text":"doesn't mean these things can't represent"},{"time":498635,"text":"other things in the real world, such as music.\""},{"time":501988,"text":"This was a huge leap, because Babbage is there saying,"},{"time":504722,"text":"\"We could compute these amazing functions and print out"},{"time":506944,"text":"tables of numbers and draw graphs,\" — (Laughter) —"},{"time":510612,"text":"and Lovelace is there and she says, \"Look,"},{"time":512508,"text":"this thing could even compose music if you"},{"time":514984,"text":"told it a representation of music numerically.\""},{"time":518532,"text":"So this is what I call Lovelace's Leap."},{"time":520101,"text":"When you say she's a programmer, she did do some,"},{"time":523838,"text":"but the real thing is to have said the future is going to be"},{"time":526975,"text":"much, much more than this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529171,"text":"Now, a hundred years later, this guy comes along,"},{"time":531350,"text":"Alan Turing, and in 1936, and invents the computer all over again."},{"time":536803,"text":"Now, of course, Babbage's machine was entirely mechanical."},{"time":539380,"text":"Turing's machine was entirely theoretical."},{"time":541911,"text":"Both of these guys were coming from a mathematical perspective,"},{"time":544702,"text":"but Turing told us something very important."},{"time":547255,"text":"He laid down the mathematical foundations"},{"time":550190,"text":"for computer science, and said,"},{"time":552303,"text":"\"It doesn't matter how you make a computer.\""},{"time":555490,"text":"It doesn't matter if your computer's mechanical,"},{"time":557368,"text":"like Babbage's was, or electronic, like computers are today,"},{"time":561778,"text":"or perhaps in the future, cells, or, again,"},{"time":564582,"text":"mechanical again, once we get into nanotechnology."},{"time":567728,"text":"We could go back to Babbage's machine"},{"time":569765,"text":"and just make it tiny. All those things are computers."},{"time":572341,"text":"There is in a sense a computing essence."},{"time":573973,"text":"This is called the Church–Turing thesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575978,"text":"And so suddenly, you get this link where you say"},{"time":578645,"text":"this thing Babbage had built really was a computer."},{"time":580868,"text":"In fact, it was capable of doing everything we do today"},{"time":583693,"text":"with computers, only really slowly. (Laughter)"},{"time":588525,"text":"To give you an idea of how slowly,"},{"time":590631,"text":"it had about 1k of memory."},{"time":594470,"text":"It used punch cards, which were being fed in,"},{"time":597388,"text":"and it ran about 10,000 times slower the first ZX81."},{"time":603148,"text":"It did have a RAM pack."},{"time":604751,"text":"You could add on a lot of extra memory if you wanted to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607930,"text":"(Laughter) So, where does that bring us today?"},{"time":610256,"text":"So there are plans."},{"time":611864,"text":"Over in Swindon, the Science Museum archives,"},{"time":614797,"text":"there are hundreds of plans and thousands of pages"},{"time":616491,"text":"of notes written by Charles Babbage about this analytical engine."},{"time":619960,"text":"One of those is a set of plans that we call Plan 28,"},{"time":623921,"text":"and that is also the name of a charity that I started"},{"time":626075,"text":"with Doron Swade, who was the curator of computing"},{"time":628809,"text":"at the Science Museum, and also the person who drove"},{"time":631048,"text":"the project to build a difference engine,"},{"time":632478,"text":"and our plan is to build it."},{"time":635036,"text":"Here in South Kensington, we will build the analytical engine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638902,"text":"The project has a number of parts to it."},{"time":640904,"text":"One was the scanning of Babbage's archive."},{"time":643424,"text":"That's been done. The second is now the study"},{"time":645346,"text":"of all of those plans to determine what to build."},{"time":648456,"text":"The third part is a computer simulation of that machine,"},{"time":652900,"text":"and the last part is to physically build it at the Science Museum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655823,"text":"When it's built, you'll finally be able to understand how a computer works,"},{"time":658399,"text":"because rather than having a tiny chip in front of you,"},{"time":660233,"text":"you've got to look at this humongous thing and say, \"Ah,"},{"time":662843,"text":"I see the memory operating, I see the CPU operating,"},{"time":666178,"text":"I hear it operating. I probably smell it operating.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":670045,"text":"But in between that we're going to do a simulation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672644,"text":"Babbage himself wrote, he said,"},{"time":674401,"text":"as soon as the analytical engine exists,"},{"time":676019,"text":"it will surely guide the future course of science."},{"time":679723,"text":"Of course, he never built it, because he was always fiddling"},{"time":681568,"text":"with new plans, but when it did get built, of course,"},{"time":683650,"text":"in the 1940s, everything changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687160,"text":"Now, I'll just give you a little taste of what it looks like"},{"time":688983,"text":"in motion with a video which shows"},{"time":691616,"text":"just one part of the CPU mechanism working."},{"time":699210,"text":"So this is just three sets of cogs,"},{"time":702209,"text":"and it's going to add. This is the adding mechanism"},{"time":705031,"text":"in action, so you imagine this gigantic machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707688,"text":"So, give me five years."},{"time":708847,"text":"Before the 2030s happen, we'll have it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711191,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}